// UI Manager
// Manages pending UI render requests and routes browser/terminal responses back to waiting MCP callers.

The session key is "{project}:{session}".
Blocking renders return a Promise that resolves when the user responds.
Non-blocking renders return immediately; callers poll getUIStatus for the result.
A singleton instance (uiManager) is exported for convenience.

FUNCTION generateUIId() -> string
  Combine current timestamp and 6 random hex digits, prefixed with "ui_".

---

FUNCTION renderUI(request) -> UIResponse (Promise)
  Validate that project, session, ui object, and ui.type are all present.
  Generate or use the provided uiId. Build the session key.
  Cache the UI as 'pending' for reconnection recovery.
  IF non-blocking, return a resolved response immediately with source='terminal'.
  IF blocking, create a Promise and store it as a pendingUI entry.
  The Promise resolves when receiveResponse is called with a matching uiId.

---

FUNCTION receiveResponse(sessionKey, uiId, response) -> boolean
  Check that a cached UI exists for the session and its uiId matches. Return false if stale or missing.
  Update the cached UI status to 'responded' and record the response.
  IF a pending Promise exists for the same uiId, resolve it with the full UIResponse and remove it.
  Return true.

---

FUNCTION getPendingUI(sessionKey) -> PendingUI | null
  Return the pending UI (unresolved blocking render) for the session, or null.

---

FUNCTION dismissUI(sessionKey) -> boolean
  IF no pending UI exists, return false.
  Mark the cached UI as 'canceled'. Reject the pending Promise with "UI dismissed".
  Remove from pending map. Return true.

---

FUNCTION getCurrentUI(sessionKey) -> CachedUI | null
  Return the most recently cached UI for the session (used for reconnection recovery), or null.

---

FUNCTION getUIStatus(project, session, uiId) -> { status, action, data }
  Build the session key. Look up the cached UI.
  IF not found, return status='not_found'.
  IF uiId does not match, return status='stale'.
  IF status is 'responded', return status='responded' with action and data from the response.
  Otherwise return status='pending'.
